definitions.definition: Someone's birth ; the place , time and circumstances of a birth.
Someone's birth considered as a means of astrology ; a horoscope associated with a person's birth.
The festival celebrating the birth of Jesus , Christmas Day ; the festival celebrating the birth of the Virgin Mary or the birth of Saint John the Baptist .
A set of figurines used to create a nativity scene .
Place of origin; place to which a species is native .
The quality of being native or innate .

main_definition: ( now dated ) Someone's birth ; the place , time and circumstances of a birth. [from 14th c.]
secondary_definitions: ( astrology ) Someone's birth considered as a means of astrology ; a horoscope associated with a person's birth. [from 14th c.]
( also with capital initial ) The birth of Jesus . [from 14th c.]

( Christianity , also with capital initial ) The festival celebrating the birth of Jesus , Christmas Day ; the festival celebrating the birth of the Virgin Mary or the birth of Saint John the Baptist . [from 12th c.]
( also with capital initial ) A set of figurines used to create a nativity scene .
Place of origin; place to which a species is native .
The quality of being native or innate .
